[00:08.47]He saw the crowd from the mountainside
[00:12.81]Every broken heart, every tear they cried
[00:17.14]Didn’t look away, didn’t pass them by
[00:21.47]Love in His eyes, hope alive
[00:25.80]He stepped right in, He reached right out
[00:30.14]Spoke healing where there was doubt
[00:34.47]Moved with compassion, strong and kind
[00:38.80]Love with the power to change a life
[00:43.14]When He speaks, the dark gives way
[00:47.47]Joy breaks out, the blind can see
[00:51.80]He lifts the weak, He calls us friends
[00:56.13]Grace that starts and never ends
[01:00.47]The King of heaven walks with us
[01:04.80]All authority, all love, all trust
[01:09.13]He touched the ones no one would hold
[01:13.46]Spoke their worth to the lost and old
[01:17.80]“Come to Me,” hear the mercy call
[01:22.13]Every chain about to fall
[01:26.46]Every word steady and true
[01:30.80]Hope rising when He moves
[01:35.13]Moved with compassion, strong and kind
[01:39.46]Love with the power to change a life
